{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CNmPNXYH3bc16E9pwAQ7VH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - there's already a `ca.key` in `/tmp/crdb-certs` from a previous run (dated Jun 24). The other certs are fresh from today (Jul 1). The new certs I generated should work fine.\n\nNow let me create the Kubernetes secrets. I need:\n1. A secret for the node certs (`cockroachdb-node`) - used by the CockroachDB pods\n2. A secret for the client root cert (optional, but useful for testing)\n\nFor CockroachDB, the standard Kubernetes secret structure is:\n- A secret containing `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, `node.key` for the nodes\n- Optionally, a separate secret for client certs\n\nThe secret needs to be mounted at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs/` in each pod. Let me create these secrets and then update the StatefulSet.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":739,"cache_read_input_tokens":35437,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":739},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a2cfedd-deef-4b4c-b890-670b3d27cbd9","uuid":"d080d96e-3b08-4145-a5be-cf2f307bd310","request_id":"req_011Ccb4gDuAWc3XH3d7ytrXx"}
