{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VTweDJz4S9eehUUL8yPgbN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both goals achieved:\n\n1. **Insecure access rejected** — `--insecure` returns `ERROR: node is running secure mode, SSL connection required` (exit 1)\n2. **Secure access succeeds** — `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs` returns `1` (exit 0)\n\n**What was done:**\n1. Used `cockroach cert` inside `crdb-cluster-0` to generate a CA cert, a shared node cert (with all 3 node DNS names as SANs), and a root client cert\n2. Created two Kubernetes secrets: `cockroachdb-node` (ca.crt + node.crt + node.key) and `cockroachdb-client-root` (ca.crt + client root certs)\n3. Patched the StatefulSet to replace `--insecure` with `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, mount the certs secret via a projected volume at that path, and switch the liveness/readiness probes from HTTP to HTTPS\n4. Scaled to 0 then back to 3 to restart all nodes simultaneously (required because CockroachDB can't operate in mixed insecure/secure mode during a rolling update)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":205,"cache_read_input_tokens":51111,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":205},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a2cfedd-deef-4b4c-b890-670b3d27cbd9","uuid":"f0034dad-9898-4849-9b44-3070f34f7e59","request_id":"req_011Ccb6bYVwtkpG9LpYxL7j1"}
